<item>
            <title>[SOLR-14628] hl.fragsizeIsMinimum default ought to be &apos;true&apos; for performance</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-14628</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;hl.fragsizeIsMinimum was added in 8.5 with a default setting of false &amp;#8211; thus producing &lt;em&gt;average&lt;/em&gt; length fragments of fragsize instead of &lt;em&gt;minimum&lt;/em&gt; beyond fragsize.  In previous releases, even though the setting didn&apos;t exist, it was in-effect true (minimum).  Unfortunately, this flip was found to be a significant performance regression for highlighting lots of text (especially when using the SENTENCE break iterator), and furthermore it seems to be of relatively minor value in fragment sizing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I propose we flip this back to true.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/r2e44d290eac9edfa61ed9eced0d9f01a7bd1cbdf910344b2aa2368b8%40%3Csolr-user.lucene.apache.org%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/r2e44d290eac9edfa61ed9eced0d9f01a7bd1cbdf910344b2aa2368b8%40%3Csolr-user.lucene.apache.org%3E&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
